org.magelan.core.entity
Class PathEntity

java.lang.Object
  org.magelan.core.DefaultEntity
      org.magelan.core.entity.PathEntity
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Entity, DrawingElement
public class PathEntity
extends DefaultEntity

PathEntity. A path is described using the concept of a current point. In an analogy with drawing on paper, the current point can be thought of as the location of the pen. The position of the pen can be changed, and the outline of a shape (open or closed) can be traced by dragging the pen in either straight lines or curves.

Paths represent an outline of an object which is defined in terms of moveto (set a new current * point), lineto (draw a straight line), curveto (draw a curve using a cubic bezier), arc (elliptical or circular arc) and closepath (close the current shape by drawing a line to the last moveto) elements. Compound paths (i.e., a path with subpaths, each consisting of a single moveto followed by one or more line or curve operations) are possible to allow effects * such as "donut holes" in objects.
